WEBVTT

00:01.389 --> 00:02.656
<i>ariel:
onomatopoeia.</i>

00:02.724 --> 00:03.658
<i>bridgette:
what a dumb word.</i>

00:03.726 --> 00:05.460
<i>i didn't ask you
to judge it.</i>

00:05.527 --> 00:07.161
I asked you
to spell it.

00:07.229 --> 00:09.497
Well, that doesn't change
the fact that it's a dumb word.

00:09.565 --> 00:12.400
I mean, you gotta wonder
what was going on in the room

00:12.468 --> 00:14.435
The day they needed
to make up that word.

00:14.503 --> 00:15.670
(chuckles)

00:15.738 --> 00:17.505
Is there really a room
where they do that?

00:17.573 --> 00:19.407
There's got to be. right?

00:19.475 --> 00:21.476
Just spell it.

00:21.543 --> 00:25.279
O-n...

00:25.347 --> 00:26.948
There's more.

00:27.016 --> 00:28.149
(air horn blares twice)

00:28.217 --> 00:29.517
Thank you, mr. truck!

00:32.421 --> 00:33.721
I don't understand.

00:33.789 --> 00:36.090
What's he honking at me for?

00:36.158 --> 00:37.825
(air horn blares twice)

00:37.893 --> 00:39.627
It's a red light!

00:39.695 --> 00:41.329
I don't control it.

00:41.397 --> 00:42.764
I'll turn when it changes!

00:42.831 --> 00:45.199
(air horn blares twice)

00:45.267 --> 00:46.968
(truck engine revs,
car horn blares)

00:47.036 --> 00:48.102
Ah, excellent.

00:48.170 --> 00:49.337
(both horns blare)

00:49.405 --> 00:51.673
(truck engine revving)

00:52.741 --> 00:55.543
Hey! hey!
hey, what's going on?

00:55.611 --> 00:56.711
Hey.

01:00.082 --> 01:01.482
Stop! stop!

01:02.751 --> 01:04.185
(tires screeching)

01:04.253 --> 01:05.687
Ariel, do something!

01:05.754 --> 01:06.688
Stop! stop!

01:06.755 --> 01:07.689
(car horns honking)

01:07.756 --> 01:08.990
(shrieks)
stop!

01:09.058 --> 01:10.858
(horn blaring)

01:10.926 --> 01:13.494
(gasps)

01:13.562 --> 01:16.998
(sighs)

01:17.066 --> 01:19.300
Talk to me.

01:19.368 --> 01:22.003
I just hate it
that she can drive.

01:22.071 --> 01:23.471
Ariel?

01:23.539 --> 01:26.307
What are you talking about?
she's a really good driver.

01:26.375 --> 01:27.875
I know.

01:27.943 --> 01:31.579
She doesn't take any big streets
to school, does she?

01:31.647 --> 01:33.114
I don't think she can take
any really big streets

01:33.182 --> 01:34.549
On the way to school.

01:34.616 --> 01:36.117
<i>i don't think there are
any really big streets</i>

01:36.185 --> 01:37.685
On the way to school.

01:37.753 --> 01:39.287
I don't think there's
even a stoplight

01:39.354 --> 01:40.888
On the way to school.

01:40.956 --> 01:43.725
Come on. allison, come on.

01:43.792 --> 01:45.059
It's 4:00 in the morning.

01:45.127 --> 01:46.394
You worked late.

01:46.462 --> 01:48.329
You only got home
an hour and a half ago.

01:48.397 --> 01:50.131
I'm sure it's just
a really bad dream.

01:50.199 --> 01:52.333
Please. come on.
go back to sleep.

01:52.401 --> 01:54.001
You're right.

01:54.069 --> 01:56.504
She couldn't go faster
than 20 miles an hour

01:56.572 --> 01:57.672
Even if she wanted to.

01:57.740 --> 01:59.440
There's a stop sign
on every corner.

01:59.508 --> 02:01.542
Exactly.

02:01.610 --> 02:04.979
Come on. you need some rest.
we both do.

02:08.817 --> 02:11.586
It's easy for you to say.

02:14.523 --> 02:16.190
(phone rings)

02:21.396 --> 02:22.797
Hello?

02:22.865 --> 02:26.567
Man:
hello. i'm looking for
an allison dubois.

02:26.635 --> 02:27.869
This is allison dubois.

02:27.936 --> 02:29.370
May i ask who's calling?

02:29.438 --> 02:31.272
I'm with the phoenix pd.

02:31.340 --> 02:32.707
Are you the owner

02:32.775 --> 02:35.643
Of a 1991 volvo station wagon,
dark cream?

02:35.711 --> 02:37.211
Is something the matter?

02:37.279 --> 02:39.046
Did you lend the vehicle
to anyone?

02:39.114 --> 02:41.149
Is it possible it's been stolen?

02:41.216 --> 02:43.317
My daughter.
my daughter has it.

02:43.385 --> 02:45.720
Why are you asking
all these questions?

02:45.788 --> 02:48.923
There's been an accident.

